Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.39,0:04:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:244396,247441}Mr. Thiers, can you explain\Nwhat the government is thinking?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.44,0:04:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:247441,251403}It's been already two months\Nsince Prussia besieged our capital.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.40,0:04:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:251403,254323}However, our soldiers\Nare sitting by doing nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.32,0:04:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:254323,258619}Soon we will run out of food supplies\Nand start dying from starvation.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.99,0:04:24.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:260996,264499}And what is it that you would\Nlike me to do, Captain Rostain?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.16,0:04:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:265167,267711}Fight the Prussian army.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.71,0:04:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:267711,271590}To cut a path that could bring food\Nto the plates of our people.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.75,0:04:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:272758,276845}Next is a roasted duck?\NI'm loving it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.84,0:04:38.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:276845,278680}Would you like\Nto join me, Captain?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.38,0:04:41.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:279389,281934}Mr. Thiers!\NYou really have some nerve.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.43,0:04:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:283435,285145}Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.57,0:05:00.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:295572,300410}{\i1}On the streets outside,\Nan unpleasant winter wind was blowing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.49,0:05:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:301495,307167}{\i1}Andréa could not hear this wind\Nover the groans of the Parisian people.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.18,0:05:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:326186,328689}There, there.\NWe'll eat something soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.74,0:05:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:345747,350502}{\i1}To Isabelle, who now lived\Nin the gorgeous Versailles,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.50,0:05:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:350502,355841}{\i1}the suffering of the Parisian people\Nwas something inconceivable.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.06,0:06:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:370063,371606}Give our Paris back!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.60,0:06:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:371606,373066}You sentenced us to death!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.06,0:06:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:373066,375694}Yeah!\NWe're taking back our city!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.95,0:06:29.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:387956,389416}Hurry up!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.41,0:06:30.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:389416,390459}Quick! Bring water!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.80,0:06:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:402804,403805}It's the army!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.23,0:06:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:416234,418195}People of Paris!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.19,0:07:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:418195,421073}Rebellion will be punished\Nwith a death penalty.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.07,0:07:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:421073,423200}Disperse immediately!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.49,0:07:05.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:424493,425994}This is not a rebellion!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.83,0:07:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:429831,431041}Geneviève?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.79,0:07:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:431792,436922}We wanted to protect our beloved Paris,\Nand went through many hardships!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.92,0:07:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:436922,440342}But you people,\Nthe army, the government,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.34,0:07:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:440342,445055}not only do not protect anything,\Nyou keep these piles of food!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.01,0:07:28.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:446014,448892}And you don't share them with anyone!\NWhat's the meaning of this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.22,0:07:30.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:449226,450268}Down with the rebels!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.52,0:07:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:453522,455023}Shoot. Shoot them!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.02,0:07:37.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:455023,457234}That's an order!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.65,0:07:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:460654,463156}{\i1}That's right.\NIt is a valid order.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.65,0:07:46.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:463657,466201}{\i1}But can you really\Nexpect them to comply,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.20,0:07:50.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:466201,470664}{\i1}to shoot their brothers and sisters who\Nlikewise only want to defend their homes?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.88,0:08:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:485887,487347}We're going back!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.51,0:08:09.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:487514,489391}But… But, Captain!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.39,0:08:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:489391,492644}Listen.\NOur opponent is Prussia.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.64,0:08:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:492644,494604}It is not our people!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.06,0:08:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:501069,502654}{\i1}Andréa…
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.16,0:08:31.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:508160,511663}If we let these savages keep running rampant,\NParis will burn down to the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.66,0:08:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:511663,513832}And so will our wealth.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.41,0:08:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:514416,519129}The best way out of this predicament\Nis to hand over the capital to the Prussians.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.12,0:08:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:519129,523008}Our condition will be\Nto leave our property intact.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.55,0:08:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:523550,527512}But what are we going to do\Nwith the Parisians, Mr. Thiers?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.01,0:08:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:528013,530348}I have an idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.14,0:08:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:531141,532893}Call the commander\Nof the garrison!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.89,0:08:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:532893,534060}Yes sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.06,0:09:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:541067,541860}Go inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.44,0:09:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:545447,546573}Did you call for me, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.44,0:09:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:547449,550660}I will give you a chance to fight\Nthe Prussian army, as you wished.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.66,0:09:12.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:550660,552996}Very soon, you will lead\Nan attack on Champigny.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.53,0:09:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:553538,555165}Yes sir.\NIt's finally happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.16,0:09:16.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:555165,556958}Yes. It finally is.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.95,0:09:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:556958,559044}I wish you good luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.04,0:09:19.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:559044,559878}Thank you, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.75,0:09:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:562756,565383}Look at that stupid kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.38,0:09:27.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:565383,567010}Panza!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.51,0:09:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:568512,569721}Did you want anything, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.72,0:09:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:569721,572390}Deliver this to the Prussian army.\NTime is of essence.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.60,0:09:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:573600,577187}{\i1}That letter contained\NAndréa's plans.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.18,0:09:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:577187,578313}{\i1}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.31,0:09:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:578313,581942}{\i1}Thiers organized a trap\Nfor his own soldiers.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.35,0:09:45.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:582359,585779}The Paris Garrison\Nwill be annihilated now.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.24,0:09:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:589241,591326}What? Andréa's unit\Nwent on a sortie?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.57,0:09:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:591576,594162}Yes. Looks like Paris\Nfinally goes on the offensive.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.16,0:09:56.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:594162,596581}Victor, what are our chances?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.58,0:09:58.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:596581,598750}It is hard to tell.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.75,0:10:00.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:598750,600627}However, it is Andréa\Nwe're talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.62,0:10:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:600627,604422}Exactly!\NHe will not be defeated.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.42,0:10:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:604422,609511}Ah… I wish I was born a boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.51,0:10:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:609511,613765}I'd help Andréa and\NI'd torn our enemies to pieces!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.76,0:10:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:613765,614808}Like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.80,0:10:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:614808,616768}Do not get\Ncarried away, Isabelle.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.10,0:10:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:617102,618228}Yes, Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.06,0:10:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:623066,626945}{\i1}December 1870.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.36,0:10:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:627362,633285}{\i1}The French troops led by Andréa\Nset out for Champigny.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.28,0:10:39.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:633285,639457}{\i1}This sortie was set up to let\Nthe rebels lose their energy to fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.45,0:10:43.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:639457,643378}{\i1}No one knew that\Nit was a miserable sacrifice.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.62,0:10:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:644629,648341}We'll be arriving at Champigny soon.\NKeep your heads on a swivel.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.71,0:10:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:648717,649676}Yes sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.67,0:10:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:649676,650635}Captain!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.26,0:10:52.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:651261,652470}How did the scout go?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.47,0:10:54.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:652470,654931}Well… I didn't see anybody!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.34,0:10:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:655348,657350}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.81,0:11:03.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:659811,663106}Not a single enemy soldier?\NWhat does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.33,0:11:20.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:678330,680290}Damn! They found us!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.29,0:11:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:680290,681666}All forces, attack!
Comment: 0,0:12:25.81,0:12:25.81,Default,[chapter],0,0,0,,{TIME:745814,745814}Part B
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.54,0:12:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:771548,773258}Andréa… Andréa!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.21,0:12:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:774217,776052}Andréa!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.93,0:13:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:787939,789357}Victor?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.35,0:13:11.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:789357,791151}Why is he so late at night?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.70,0:13:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:799701,801369}I am very sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.36,0:13:24.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:801369,804789}In the Battle of Champigny,\Nour French troops
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.78,0:13:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:804789,806958}were completely annihilated.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.95,0:13:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:806958,809961}Andréa has lost his life\Nin a just cause.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.00,0:13:35.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:813006,815091}No way… No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.42,0:13:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:816426,818845}It's a joke, right? Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.84,0:13:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:818845,820221}Somebody…
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.22,0:13:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:820221,821848}Somebody tell me\Nit's a bad joke!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.72,0:13:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:822724,826311}Victor… Please,\Ntell me it's not true.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.32,0:14:00.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:839324,840575}Andréa…
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.87,0:14:07.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:845872,847874}It can't be true!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.13,0:14:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:858134,859219}Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.42,0:14:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:861429,865308}{\i1}January 1871.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.30,0:14:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:865308,871356}{\i1}The Prussian army that had besieged Paris\Nfinally launched an attack on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.07,0:14:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:878071,879948}Somebody help us!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.57,0:14:44.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:881574,884744}It's burning like hell…
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.24,0:14:49.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:885245,889332}That territory is unrelated\Nto our property.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.33,0:14:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:889332,893127}How lovely to finally see\Nthose ugly slums burn to ashes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.71,0:14:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:893711,899008}Now is the best time\Nto surrender to the Prussians.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.80,0:15:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:900802,902720}We have to put out the fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.72,0:15:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:902720,904889}Don't panic! Bring some water!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.97,0:15:09.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:908977,909936}We can do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.23,0:15:14.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:913231,914691}Hurry up!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.69,0:15:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:914691,915900}Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.48,0:15:18.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:917485,918736}Just a little more!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.73,0:15:20.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:918736,920196}What are you doing? Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.20,0:16:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:971205,973124}Isabelle.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.12,0:16:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:973124,975043}Father?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.04,0:16:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:979047,981007}Isabelle, listen to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.00,0:16:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:981007,983593}I want to cry all the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.59,0:16:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:983593,986638}However, the one who has it\Nthe worst is your mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.63,0:16:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:986638,988848}Geneviève had left our house.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.84,0:16:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:988848,990975}And now Andréa\Nhas passed away.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.97,0:16:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:990975,994646}Isabelle, you are all\Nthat's left for her.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.64,0:16:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:994646,997482}Promise me that you will not\Nmake your mother any sadder.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.77,0:16:42.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:999776,1002195}The three of us\Nmust not be destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.19,0:16:45.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1002195,1005156}You are the only descendant\Nto the Rostain family now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.82,0:16:47.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1005823,1007992}Isabelle.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.61,0:16:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1008618,1011829}No matter what you say\Nabout Jean, he is a noble.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.88,0:17:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1029889,1031349}I'm touched.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.34,0:17:14.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1031349,1034435}It's the first time in my life\Nthat you've called me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.43,0:17:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1034435,1035645}What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.18,0:17:19.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1038189,1039315}Isabelle?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.81,0:17:23.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1039816,1043236}Jean, when I was little,\NI made a decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.23,0:17:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1043236,1047198}If I am ever going to marry anybody,\Nhe must be stronger than me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.19,0:17:30.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1047198,1050952}I hate crybabies such as yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.95,0:17:34.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1051953,1054038}I'm not what I used to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.62,0:17:36.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1054622,1056124}Can you win with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.33,0:17:38.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1056332,1058459}Who knows? I might lose.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.46,0:17:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1062463,1064590}Looks like you've gotten\Na bit stronger.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.34,0:17:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1067343,1070805}Isabelle, you're scaring me!\NWhat happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.60,0:18:00.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1079605,1080815}Hop!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.03,0:18:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1090033,1091576}I lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.57,0:18:13.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1091576,1093453}Practice makes perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.45,0:18:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1093453,1096205}Now you can see that\NI'm different than I used to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.83,0:18:21.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1098833,1101419}Now, now. That's it for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.42,0:18:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1102420,1103838}I'm leaving.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.00,0:18:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1106007,1108259}Hop… Ahh!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.05,0:18:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1110053,1112388}Did I overdo it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.38,0:18:34.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1112388,1114015}That's just so you, Jean.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.94,0:18:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1126944,1131115}Our homes and the city\Nburned down to the foundations.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.11,0:18:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1131115,1133868}Look at it another way,\NGeneviève.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.86,0:18:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1133868,1135953}See? We're still alive!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.95,0:18:58.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1135953,1138831}This is our town,\Nfor as long as we live.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.29,0:19:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1139290,1143836}Wise words, young lad.\NWe can always just rebuild it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.83,0:19:05.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1143836,1145338}Right, everyone?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.33,0:19:06.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1145338,1146130}Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.13,0:19:08.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1146130,1148299}Big news, big news, big news!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.29,0:19:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1148299,1151135}Paris lost! Paris lost!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.13,0:19:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1151135,1151969}What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.96,0:19:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1151969,1155098}Paris officially lost.\NWe've surrendered!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.09,0:19:20.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1155098,1160061}That son of a gun, Thiers,\Nsold our city to the Prussians!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.03,0:19:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1176035,1178037}{\i1}Paris surrendered.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.66,0:19:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1178663,1184252}{\i1}It was Thiers' scheming,\Nto protect his estate.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.63,0:19:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1188631,1193052}{\i1}When the Prussian troops\Nmarched into the city, the citizens of Paris
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.05,0:19:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1193052,1196889}{\i1}made a silent protest\Nby shutting down the windows.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.22,0:20:00.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1198224,1200351}Did they really surrender?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.35,0:20:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1200351,1201769}I have a bad feeling about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.64,0:20:09.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1205648,1209026}Is this really Paris?\NThe capital of beauty and art?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.90,0:20:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1209902,1212905}Everything is shut.\NThey reject us.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.82,0:20:16.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1214824,1216534}Away with the Prussians!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.53,0:20:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1216534,1218161}Leave our city!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.37,0:20:21.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1219370,1221706}Leave our city!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.70,0:20:23.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1221706,1223291}Leave it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.29,0:20:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1223291,1224500}You insolent peasant!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.50,0:20:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1224500,1227962}Don't even think about it!\NWe are the proud Prussian soldiers.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.96,0:20:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1227962,1229505}We are not child murderers!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.50,0:20:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1231507,1233593}Paris has not yet surrendered.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.59,0:20:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1238598,1241100}Not yet surrendered?\NWhat do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.60,0:20:45.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1241601,1245980}It seems that the surrender of Paris\Nwas just your arbitrary decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.98,0:20:49.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1245980,1249859}As things stand, we cannot\Nstation our army here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.85,0:20:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1249859,1252403}I am a Paris representative!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.40,0:20:57.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1252403,1257742}I cannot trust a representative whose\Nopinions do not align with his people's.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.74,0:21:00.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1257742,1260203}I pray that your citizens\Ndo not unleash their wrath.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.99,0:21:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1260995,1263122}I advise you to be careful\Nin future endeavors.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.74,0:21:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1263748,1264498}Well, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.25,0:21:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1267251,1269420}{\i1}Citizens unleashing their wrath…
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.09,0:21:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1275092,1276260}Away with Thiers!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.26,0:21:18.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1276260,1278137}Banish him!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.55,0:21:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1281557,1284185}Let's defend our city!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.18,0:21:25.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1284185,1285561}Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.56,0:21:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1285561,1289148}Our enemies leisurely walk\Nthe streets of our city. I've had enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.56,0:21:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1289565,1291234}Damn right!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.23,0:21:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1291234,1294028}Thiers sold our city to the Prussians!\NHe's our enemy!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.36,0:21:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1294362,1295780}Damn right!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.78,0:21:37.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1295780,1297406}Away with Thiers!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.40,0:21:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1297406,1300034}We will defend\Nour city ourselves!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.03,0:21:41.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1300034,1301410}Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.41,0:21:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1301410,1303204}Let's protect it together!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.91,0:21:45.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1304914,1305998}Protect Paris!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.54,0:21:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1308542,1310002}Protect Paris!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.67,0:21:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1311671,1312797}Away with Thiers!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.84,0:21:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1316842,1319303}As if I let them\Ndo as they please!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.63,0:22:03.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1320638,1323224}Sir, a big problem! The people\Ngathered in front of the building!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.01,0:22:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1324016,1328020}What? They must be forgetting\Nwho they are. Make them disperse!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.31,0:22:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1330314,1332608}What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.70,0:22:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1341701,1342868}We're going to escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.86,0:22:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1342868,1344537}Escape? Where to?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.53,0:22:26.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1344537,1346747}We will ask the Prussians\Nfor asylum, you fool!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.29,0:22:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1347290,1349625}The Prussians?\NWe're going to ask our enemy for help?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.00,0:22:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1350001,1352795}Look at their numbers. Do you see\Nhow many of them are down there?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.79,0:22:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1352795,1354714}They're scarier than the enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.71,0:22:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1354714,1357008}Follow me.\NWe'll take the back door.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.00,0:22:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1357008,1358175}Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.22,0:22:44.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1361220,1364890}{\i1}March 1871.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.89,0:22:50.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1364890,1370896}{\i1}Thiers, fearing the wrath of the Parisians,\Nsought help from the Prussian army
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.89,0:22:53.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1370896,1373774}{\i1}and fled away to Versailles.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.19,0:23:00.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1377194,1380656}Mark my words, you scoundrels!\NI'll make you pay for this!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.15,0:23:03.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1381157,1383743}What? Thiers fled Paris?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.53,0:23:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1384535,1386787}So what is going on there now?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.78,0:23:10.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1386787,1390624}Only a handful of soldiers is still\Ntrying to defend Paris and its people.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.20,0:23:15.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1391208,1395296}Unfortunately, none of them\Nare as good as Andréa.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.29,0:23:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1396297,1399133}How are Sister and Jules?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.22,0:23:33.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1411228,1413397}{\i1}What is going to happen to Paris?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.60,0:23:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1413606,1415691}{\i1}Jules…
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.69,0:23:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1415691,1417735}{\i1}Sister…
